	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Website: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://affinix.com/">http://affinix.com/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />&quot;Infinity&quot; was a Game Boy color game in development in 2001 by a team including veteran TI-8x programmers Justin Karneges and Hideaki Omuro.  They were unable to find a publisher at the time, and the game languished for the next 15 years unchanged.  Finally, they decided to release the unfinished game with full source code.

		

